[{"_id": "6wDJBKKarx58JKZZ4", "postedAt": "2022-11-01T16:34:00.946Z", "postId": "AmLtDwKpduvLbCfme", "htmlBody": "<p>Moderator comments behave weirdly in dark mode</p>", "parentCommentId": null, "user": {"username": "edoarad"}}, {"_id": "QBPLj4hoSeekfvyTv", "postedAt": "2022-11-01T16:37:53.153Z", "postId": "AmLtDwKpduvLbCfme", "htmlBody": "<p><a href=\"https://forum.effectivealtruism.org/posts/nDgCKwjBKwFvcBsts/corporate-campaigns-for-chicken-welfare-are-10-000-times-as#Cost_effectiveness_of_GiveWell_s_Maximum_Impact_Fund1\">https://forum.effectivealtruism.org/posts/nDgCKwjBKwFvcBsts/corporate-campaigns-for-chicken-welfare-are-10-000-times-as#Cost_effectiveness_of_GiveWell_s_Maximum_Impact_Fund1</a></p><p>Tables:</p><figure class=\"image\"><img src=\"https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/f225a37347c2b215e80f354c69bbad29fe31428e0bdd70b9.png\" srcset=\"https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/f225a37347c2b215e80f354c69bbad29fe31428e0bdd70b9.png/w_90 90w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/f225a37347c2b215e80f354c69bbad29fe31428e0bdd70b9.png/w_180 180w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/f225a37347c2b215e80f354c69bbad29fe31428e0bdd70b9.png/w_270 270w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/f225a37347c2b215e80f354c69bbad29fe31428e0bdd70b9.png/w_360 360w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/f225a37347c2b215e80f354c69bbad29fe31428e0bdd70b9.png/w_450 450w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/f225a37347c2b215e80f354c69bbad29fe31428e0bdd70b9.png/w_540 540w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/f225a37347c2b215e80f354c69bbad29fe31428e0bdd70b9.png/w_630 630w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/f225a37347c2b215e80f354c69bbad29fe31428e0bdd70b9.png/w_720 720w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/f225a37347c2b215e80f354c69bbad29fe31428e0bdd70b9.png/w_810 810w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/f225a37347c2b215e80f354c69bbad29fe31428e0bdd70b9.png/w_862 862w\"></figure>", "parentCommentId": null, "user": {"username": "edoarad"}}, {"_id": "2N5o67rSDR662pbPJ", "postedAt": "2022-11-01T17:06:22.182Z", "postId": "AmLtDwKpduvLbCfme", "htmlBody": "<p>If possible, an easier way to change between dark/light mode, like a switch on the top right menu, would be great. &nbsp;</p>", "parentCommentId": null, "user": {"username": "renanaraujo"}}, {"_id": "eXsAhWjveqK8Tjnk9", "postedAt": "2022-11-01T21:47:57.264Z", "postId": "AmLtDwKpduvLbCfme", "htmlBody": "<p>Can I ask what use case you have for this? Are you switching it multiple times a day (like with sunrise-sunset? If so, can I ask what operating system you're using?</p>", "parentCommentId": "2N5o67rSDR662pbPJ", "user": {"username": "jpaddison"}}, {"_id": "FPZz6c6RECqTcoRmv", "postedAt": "2022-11-02T01:48:48.575Z", "postId": "AmLtDwKpduvLbCfme", "htmlBody": "<p>Just wanted to say it looks really good! Especially on mobile! Good work!</p>\n", "parentCommentId": null, "user": {"username": "Peter_Hurford"}}, {"_id": "5rMgPeyJBQnpfoBBW", "postedAt": "2022-11-02T02:28:03.331Z", "postId": "AmLtDwKpduvLbCfme", "htmlBody": "<p>I\u2019d switch depending on the time of day, device I\u2019m using (phone or computer),  and lighting situation, as I read the forum a lot on the go. I use Chrome and Firefox.</p>\n", "parentCommentId": "eXsAhWjveqK8Tjnk9", "user": {"username": "renanaraujo"}}, {"_id": "hRcWaXD7nnpmWXTE9", "postedAt": "2022-11-02T02:49:11.668Z", "postId": "AmLtDwKpduvLbCfme", "htmlBody": "<p>On Mac, Windows, Android, iOS?</p>\n", "parentCommentId": "5rMgPeyJBQnpfoBBW", "user": {"username": "jpaddison"}}, {"_id": "xLz2WXpCmGqJuguZm", "postedAt": "2022-11-02T14:17:45.913Z", "postId": "AmLtDwKpduvLbCfme", "htmlBody": "<p>Windows and iOS. (I now realize you asked for the OS and I read browser , sorry)</p>", "parentCommentId": "hRcWaXD7nnpmWXTE9", "user": {"username": "renanaraujo"}}, {"_id": "PfjpvisrpvTn8j3ic", "postedAt": "2022-11-02T20:42:59.133Z", "postId": "AmLtDwKpduvLbCfme", "htmlBody": "<p>Mac, Android and iOS already have a version of dark mode that changes on the time of day. You can then set your EA Forum them to \"Auto\" and forget it. Unfortunately, windows doesn't have such a mode, but you might find <a href=\"https://github.com/AutoDarkMode/Windows-Auto-Night-Mode\">this</a> does the job.</p><p>I'd be curious for more info about your non-time of day lighting desires, but would need to hear of more examples of this before devoting such prime real estate to something that right now I'm modeling as pretty niche.</p>", "parentCommentId": "xLz2WXpCmGqJuguZm", "user": {"username": "jpaddison"}}, {"_id": "SMuQFN7MB868KcrL5", "postedAt": "2022-11-02T21:22:22.581Z", "postId": "AmLtDwKpduvLbCfme", "htmlBody": "<p>Dark mode is too stronk, especially on mobile phones.</p><p>The background is too dark (<s>it's literally black)</s> and the the text is too close to white.</p><p>Notes:</p><ul><li>This is most painful on mobile phones, where screen brightness is sort of set for consumption of media, not for productivity and long reading.</li><li>For dark color schemas that are moderate, very successful implementations of dark mode are in Apple iPhone \"Reader mode\" and Apollo:</li></ul><figure class=\"image image_resized\" style=\"width:73.06%\"><img src=\"https://media.idownloadblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Books-Appearance-Dark-Mode-iPhone.jpg\"></figure><figure class=\"image image_resized\" style=\"width:41.84%\"><img src=\"https://external-preview.redd.it/_yFkHTCW_eKSIMClKUfWicv8FS7cQlb-94AJMgufuvM.jpg?auto=webp&amp;s=f386fe421c7d2ede2cf597018143df60aaafad00\"></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Here is a good suggested setting (from Apple reader):</p><figure class=\"image image_resized\" style=\"width:41.68%\"><img src=\"https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/5219106358b55e6b1b346f0423330c103cc457b0a5a42cba.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/5219106358b55e6b1b346f0423330c103cc457b0a5a42cba.jpeg/w_100 100w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/5219106358b55e6b1b346f0423330c103cc457b0a5a42cba.jpeg/w_180 180w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/5219106358b55e6b1b346f0423330c103cc457b0a5a42cba.jpeg/w_260 260w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/5219106358b55e6b1b346f0423330c103cc457b0a5a42cba.jpeg/w_340 340w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/5219106358b55e6b1b346f0423330c103cc457b0a5a42cba.jpeg/w_420 420w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/5219106358b55e6b1b346f0423330c103cc457b0a5a42cba.jpeg/w_500 500w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/5219106358b55e6b1b346f0423330c103cc457b0a5a42cba.jpeg/w_580 580w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/5219106358b55e6b1b346f0423330c103cc457b0a5a42cba.jpeg/w_660 660w, https://39669.cdn.cke-cs.com/cgyAlfpLFBBiEjoXacnz/images/5219106358b55e6b1b346f0423330c103cc457b0a5a42cba.jpeg/w_740 740w\"></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Adding flavors of dark mode seems good.</p><ul><li>Solving this by brightening the background somewhat, will help with the issue that many graphs/graphics are white and really pop out of a black background.</li></ul>", "parentCommentId": null, "user": {"username": "Charles He"}}, {"_id": "zNJcvpjd2YRwgqoo4", "postedAt": "2022-11-03T10:34:15.349Z", "postId": "AmLtDwKpduvLbCfme", "htmlBody": "<p>This (and your other comment about tables in posts) should now be fixed - thanks for letting us know!</p>", "parentCommentId": "6wDJBKKarx58JKZZ4", "user": {"username": "Ollie Etherington"}}, {"_id": "PhFiftbE5qDyW72Bh", "postedAt": "2022-11-03T11:57:10.049Z", "postId": "AmLtDwKpduvLbCfme", "htmlBody": "<p>Some situations in which I appreciate light/dark switches in general:</p><ul><li>It's day, but I'm in my room on my phone and it's dark.</li><li>It's night, but I'm in my computer with sufficient light around me.</li><li>I'm on the tube and it's lighter or I'm in a car and it's darker than outside.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>But I know your time is quite valuable and I don't have a good sense of how effortful it'd be to implement this, so take this suggestion as something I'd consider nice-to-have but have absolutely no strong feelings about it.&nbsp;</p>", "parentCommentId": "PfjpvisrpvTn8j3ic", "user": {"username": "renanaraujo"}}, {"_id": "x2yexZi42E9xA3e74", "postedAt": "2022-11-03T18:06:47.195Z", "postId": "AmLtDwKpduvLbCfme", "htmlBody": "<p>Thank you! \ud83d\udc96</p>", "parentCommentId": "zNJcvpjd2YRwgqoo4", "user": {"username": "edoarad"}}, {"_id": "FwrqmLR7YwxQ76tfF", "postedAt": "2022-11-02T23:05:22.992Z", "postId": "AmLtDwKpduvLbCfme", "htmlBody": null, "parentCommentId": "SMuQFN7MB868KcrL5", "user": null}]